WRITING.TEXT: Here is more about it http://www.vintagesynth.com/misc/neuron.php

If your close to NY i can donate 2 korg poly 61's to your project.
One works good one key fucked up. The other the battery burst ....cost was estimated at 50 dollars to fix each.
The arpeggiator alone is worth having.
Anyways great board for sounds ....the discovery kinda sucks but you get used to it.
Also if your on a budget go to estate sales, salvation army and tag sales etc.
Those crappy organs that people throw away have some good sounds. I bought a poly 61 for 20 dollars at a tag sale. Old Casio boards in the 80's sell cheap EG~ the CZ series.
Anyways I am just suggesting you guys do some research. because there is nothing like true analog sounds... they blend together (fucking amazingly!)

I like what your doing.
I just am not to keen on the synth sounds, as a musician myself i guess i have more a liking to analog synth sounds.
Grab a Korg poly 61 there cheap. a bitch to use but i think that's what you guys need... some analog love.
That's just my opinion and the only reason i say that is because you compare yourselves to sounding like BoC.....so i had expectations of lush analog synth sounds.
Your layering is inspired by BoC and i like that however i feel it falls soulfully flat as a tribute band to BoC.
Keep playing I'd be interested to here how you guys progress.
